From dd2c440323f86f58a59cdf4215efb7136c4c9247 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sowmiya Sree Elavalagan <ssreeela@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 27 Nov 2025 11:15:27 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:hostapd: Reset SA Query timeout after STA
 clean up.

When an MLD station attempts to reassociate after an SA Query
timeout, hostapd cleans up partner links and removes the STA from
the driver in handle_assoc. This triggers a full deletion and
re-addition of the station, delaying the association response by
~400+ms and causing the association to fail.
On subsequent reconnect attempts in handle_auth, partner links
are cleaned and the association link is re-added. However, since
sa_query_timeout is not reset, the station is cleaned up again
during association, including the main link. Partner links are
then added directly in the driver, which rejects them because the
main STA is missing. The STA eventually degrades to a single-link
connection.
Fix this issue by resetting sa_query_timeout after STA is cleaned up
for fresh connection.

Patch-dependency: s021-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Support-MLD-STA-reconnecti.patch
Patch-work: NA
Signed-off-by: Sowmiya Sree Elavalagan <ssreeela@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/ap/ieee802_11.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
+++ b/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
@@ -6519,6 +6519,7 @@ static void handle_assoc(struct hostapd_
 		hostapd_drv_sta_remove(hapd, sta->addr);
 		sta->flags &= ~(WLAN_STA_ASSOC | WLAN_STA_AUTHORIZED);
 		sta->unadded_sta = false;
+		ap_sta_set_sa_query_timeout(hapd, sta, 0);
 
 		if (ieee802_11_parse_elems(pos, left, &elems, 1) == ParseFailed) {
 			wpa_printf(MSG_DEBUG, "FT: Failed to parse elements");
